race.comment: LOUD (11) pushed forward last time and boxed on to finish a narrow second over 1200m at Warren. Has the speed to get across from the draw with Stiff's claim. Can return to the winner's circle. KUROSHINZO (10) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start when fourth over 1600m at Warren. Back in trip and finds a nice race. Value contender. ELITE POWER (3) accounted for a maiden field in good style on resumption over 1200m at Warren. Sparingly raced and has more to offer. DERVINIA (8) hit the frame two starts ago at Bathurst but ran below par last time when ninth over 1200m at Narromine. Drawn out again and can sneak into minor money.
